                <div class="stlgd-section-heading js-stlgd-page-section" id="utilityclasses">
                    <h1 class="stlgd-section-heading__cont" title="Getting started">Utility classes</h1>
                </div>
                <div class="stlgd-section-content">
                    <div class="stlgd-section-content__content stlgd-section-content__content--med">
                        <p class="stlgd-section-content__intro-text">
                            Utility classes are as simple, independent, and reusable as possible; A utility class applies a single rule or a very simple,
                            universal pattern. Think
                            <code>.float-right</code>,
                            <code>.align-center</code>, or
                            <code>.font-small</code> for single rules;
                            <code>.list-unstyled</code>, and
                            <code>.visually-hidden</code> for patterns. Sometimes they’re called “helpers”. Prefix to denote utilities, overrides,
                            and helper classes. Classes beginning with
                            <code>.u-</code> should never be redefined, bound onto, or modified.
                        </p>

                        <h2 class="stlgd-section-content__heading stlgd-section-content__heading--large">.occlss-u-hidden</h2>
                        <p>
                            This class will hide object from display
                        </p>

                        <h2 class="stlgd-section-content__heading stlgd-section-content__heading--large">.occlss-u-visuallyhidden</h2>
                        <p>
                            This class will hide object from display but it will be visable for screen readers
                        </p>

                        <h2 class="stlgd-section-content__heading stlgd-section-content__heading--large">.occlss-u-more-link</h2>
                        <p>
                            This class will apply style to the links that should be with the arrow icon on the right or left </p>
                        <p>
                            <a href="https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/cms/public-site/contact-oxfordshire-county-council" class="occlss-u-more-link">
                                Contact us
                                <span class="occlss-icon occlss-icon--arrow-right-long-right-secondary" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg aria-hidden="true" class="occlss-icon__container occlss-u-more-link__icon">
                                        <use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="../../images/occlss-sprite.svg#arrow-right-long-right-secondary"
                                            class="icon__source icon__source--svg"></use>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </a>
                        </p>

                        <h2 class="stlgd-section-content__heading stlgd-section-content__heading--large">.occlss-u-unstyled-list</h2>
                        <p>
                            This class will remove default list item style
                        </p>

                        <h2 class="stlgd-section-content__heading stlgd-section-content__heading--large">.occlss-u-max-width-&lt;n&gt;</h2>
                        <p>
                            This classes add max-width to the objects
                        </p>
                        <ul class="occlss-u-unstyled-list">
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-max-width-one-quarter</strong> - max width: 25%</li>
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-max-width-one-third</strong> - max width: 33.333%</li>
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-max-width-one-half</strong> - max width: 50%</li>
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-max-width-two-thirds</strong> - max width: 66.666%</li>
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-max-width-three-quarters</strong> - max width: 75%</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2 class="stlgd-section-content__heading stlgd-section-content__heading--large">.occlss-u-tspace-&lt;n&gt;</h2>
                        <p>
                            This classes will add top margin to the object
                        </p>
                        <ul class="occlss-u-unstyled-list">
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-tspace-none</strong> - top margin: 0</li>
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-tspace-xs</strong> - top margin: 6px</li>
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-tspace-sm</strong> - top margin: 12px</li>
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-tspace-md</strong> - top margin: 25px</li>
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-tspace-large</strong> - top margin: 50px</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2 class="stlgd-section-content__heading stlgd-section-content__heading--large">.occlss-u-bspace-&lt;n&gt;</h2>
                        <p>
                            This classes will add bottom margin to the object
                        </p>
                        <ul class="occlss-u-unstyled-list">
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-bspace-none</strong> - bottom margin: 0</li>
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-bspace-xs</strong> - bottom margin: 6px</li>
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-bspace-sm</strong> - bottom margin: 12px</li>
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-bspace-md</strong> - bottom margin: 25px</li>
                            <li><strong>.occlss-u-bspace-large</strong> - bottom margin: 50px</li>
                        </ul>

                    <h2 class="stlgd-section-content__heading stlgd-section-content__heading--large">.occlss-u-tpspace-&lt;n&gt;</h2>
                        <p>
                            This classes will add top padding to the object
